b27bd071-9537-46a0-af0f-2b4912e6de64

bcc1c97c-6078-4daf-9a3b-eb1b4fcbf3c5

ebfa470a-30af-4c20-aa96-a11e75ccd4ca

ebfa470a-30af-4c20-aa96-a11e75ccd4ca
Assemble pizza by spreading 1/4 of a cup tomato sauce on each pizza base, top with vegetables, and drizzle with a bit of chipotle sauce.
ebfa470a-30af-4c20-aa96-a11e75ccd4ca
Bake in oven for 10 minutes.
ebfa470a-30af-4c20-aa96-a11e75ccd4ca
Serve hot and drizzle with more chipotle sauce and sprinkle with fresh cilantro if desired.

Prepare asparagus by snapping off the ends at the normal breaking point. Toss ends. Using a peeler, peel the first layer of skin off the asparagus. Cut asparagus into 2 inch pieces and blanch for 2 minutes. Cool asparagus under cold water to stop cooking. Set aside.
ba1e95b6-63d3-4b58-b356-3a4bcb9d8cdf
In a large stock pot or sauté pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Sauté shallots for 2 minutes. Add garlic and risotto rice. Sauté until edges of rice turn slightly translucent (roughly 4 minutes).
ba1e95b6-63d3-4b58-b356-3a4bcb9d8cdf
Stir in white wine until absorbed by rice. Then add broth 3/4 of a cup at a time, stirring occasionally, adding more once absorbed by rice. Stir in chopped parsley and lemon zest before adding last 3/4 of a cup broth.
ba1e95b6-63d3-4b58-b356-3a4bcb9d8cdf
Stir asparagus into risotto until hot.
ba1e95b6-63d3-4b58-b356-3a4bcb9d8cdf
Remove pan from heat and garnish risotto with more parsley, fresh cracked pepper and lemon juice to taste.
6a08c265-0a66-410b-aaca-da3b3215d391

6a08c265-0a66-410b-aaca-da3b3215d391
Heat olive oil over medium heat in a saute pan. Add minced garlic and salt and saute for 2 minutes. Add sliced bell peppers and cook covered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until bell peppers have softened. Add cooked green beans and cook for another 2 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.
6a08c265-0a66-410b-aaca-da3b3215d391
Meanwhile, chop tomatoes, lettuce and onion. Set aside.
6a08c265-0a66-410b-aaca-da3b3215d391
Prepare easy guacamole. Mash avocado in a bowl with a fork. Mix in salt, cilantro, lime juice, and red pepper flakes.

Assemble tacos by spreading VFR's Taco Sauce on tortilla or on bottom of taco shell, top with lettuce, tomato, onion, then add Green bean-bell pepper mixture, and top with easy guacamole.
6a08c265-0a66-410b-aaca-da3b3215d391
Eat immediately.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Vegan Mayo Place all ingredients in a food processor or high powdered blender. Blend until smooth.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Vegan Mayo Add a few drops of hot sauce to make this a spicy vegan mayo.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Vegan Mayo Store in refrigerator, covered, for up to a week.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Eggplant Burger Slice the eggplant into 1/2" slices. Rub each slice with salt. Set aside.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Eggplant Burger In a medium sized bowl, mix together chia seeds, coconut flour, and garlic powder. Set aside.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Eggplant Burger Rinse eggplant with cold water and pat dry with a paper towel.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Eggplant Burger Coat each eggplant slice by dipping it in the flour mixture. For a ticker coating, dip in flour mixture then in almond milk, and again in the flour mixture.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Eggplant Burger Fry coated eggplant in a pan over medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and let rest on a paper towel for 5 minutes.Repeat until all eggplant slices are cooked.
45a8d3cb-fc1b-44b2-8387-35932be65a22 Eggplant Burger Assemble burgers by spreading smashed avocado on the bottom burger bun and the vegan mayo on the top bun. Add two slices of cooked eggplant on top the avocado and top with tomato, onion, and lettuce. Place top bun on top and enjoy!

325f4ed1-6fa2-4544-a82b-df44112a0ead

325f4ed1-6fa2-4544-a82b-df44112a0ead
Place your mushrooms evenly within the border of your puff pastry sheet. Try to not add to much of the extra mushroom liquid in the pan. Top with 3 rosemary springs and brush with small amount of olive oil.
325f4ed1-6fa2-4544-a82b-df44112a0ead
Carefully slide puff pastry onto the now hot baking sheet in the oven. Cook for 20 minutes or until puff pastry is golden brown.
8206f383-405e-40a3-ae84-559d0b18fe52

8206f383-405e-40a3-ae84-559d0b18fe52

8206f383-405e-40a3-ae84-559d0b18fe52

Add almond or oat milk to tomatoes, bring to a quick boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 3-5 minutes until mixture slightly thickens.
8206f383-405e-40a3-ae84-559d0b18fe52
Stir in cooked pasta shells and white wine vinegar to tomato-tempeh mixture.Pour into a large baking dish or casserole and sprinkle with crumbled cashew cheese. Drizzle with olive oil and bake on middle rack of oven for 5 minutes until bubbling and cashew cheese has browned.
8206f383-405e-40a3-ae84-559d0b18fe52

Cook Beluga Lentils according to packaging.

Prepare Jalapeno cream by placing coconut cream, jalapeno, and lime juice in a food processor. Pulse until smooth. Refrigerate jalapeno cream until ready to serve.
1afcea31-ba7c-4af1-8027-6af82cf58e83
Heat tacos according to instructions on packaging.

Once Lentils are fully cooked stir in salt, smoked paprika, cumin, and lime juice.
1afcea31-ba7c-4af1-8027-6af82cf58e83

b5831a22-9e1c-4f1b-b4d9-48ebffa72729
Heat Olive oil in a large deep fry pan and add onion with dash of salt. Saute until translucent, then add garlic and jalapeno. Saute for 1-2 more minutes.
b5831a22-9e1c-4f1b-b4d9-48ebffa72729
Add sweet potato, zucchini, corn, and tomatoes. Saute for a further 2 minutes.
b5831a22-9e1c-4f1b-b4d9-48ebffa72729
Stir in rice and add tomato puree. Slowly add vegetable broth without stirring, adding just enough to cover all ingredients. Again, DON'T STIR!

Top with herbs, and add a bit of pepper.

Cover and let simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
b5831a22-9e1c-4f1b-b4d9-48ebffa72729

b5831a22-9e1c-4f1b-b4d9-48ebffa72729

Heat oven to 395F (200C) and line sheet pan with baking paper.

Take butternut squash out of oven and further hallow out the squash. Leaving about 1/4 to 1/2 inch squash around the edges. Add squash flesh to tempeh mixture.

Fill tempeh mixture into squash, drizzle with olive oil and cook in oven (lower rack) for another 10 minutes.

a9ec9290-86b2-4644-af4d-cf594e878247
Remove Pizza from oven. Adults will enjoy this pizza topped with fresh cracked pepper. Serve hot and Enjoy!

bfeee04a-5076-4b82-99cf-6426979aad2f
Serve while still hot with Mango Vinaigrette or as a burger and enjoy!

Bring to boil.

6e3a9ea2-b1f8-4fc8-865e-0c1adf42b1f0
Serve hot, garnish will remaining cilantro and jalapeno(optional) and a spritz of fresh lime juice (optional). Enjoy!

Blend soup with an immersion blender or transfer to a blender to purée in there.

Mix with an electric mixer on low speed until the mixture is completely blended.
8bb6c938-b815-4842-afcf-d80f99d0bbf9

8bb6c938-b815-4842-afcf-d80f99d0bbf9

Place a 7 inch (18cm) Springform on a sheet of parchment paper. Trace a circle around it and cut it out. Place the parchment paper circle and springform aside.
706e3af6-1093-47dd-80a3-2085786f186e
Prepare crust by pulsing dates and almonds in a food processor until a sticky mass forms. Press this into the base of the springform.
706e3af6-1093-47dd-80a3-2085786f186e
Clean out food processor and add coconut cream and frozen strawberries. Pulse until smooth. Add up to 1(3 of a cup coconut water if food processor is having difficulties. Taste filling and add a sweetener of choice (I prefer maple syrup) if it is not sweet enough to your liking. This all depends on the sweetness of the strawberries to begin with. 706e3af6-1093-47dd-80a3-2085786f186e

Garnish with 12 small strawberries or more if desired.

2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Loaf Cake Add melted butter or coconut oil, milk, and lemon juice to flour mixture and stir together.
2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Loaf Cake Pour into prepared loaf pan and bake on lower rack for 50 to 60 minutes or until skewer comes out clean.
2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Loaf Cake Remove pan from oven and allow to cool for 10 minutes before removing cake from pan. Allow cake to fully cool on a cooling rack.
2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Coconut Oil Frosting Cream together coconut oil, lemon juice, and lemon zest.
2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Coconut Oil Frosting Add salt and 1/2 cup powdered sugar and beat together on medium speed, slowly adding more and more powdered sugar until desired consistency is achieved.
2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Coconut Oil Frosting Spread lemon frosting over cooled lemon loaf.
2631673d-565f-432b-8c54-ff607cef29fb Lemon Coconut Oil Frosting Keep lemon loaf in fridge and eat within 5 days.

5e37e720-02ab-499c-8c29-8f227331d48e
Prepare crust by pulsing dates, walnuts, and salt in a food processor until a sticky mass forms. Press the walnut-date mixture into the bottom of your springform .
5e37e720-02ab-499c-8c29-8f227331d48e

5e37e720-02ab-499c-8c29-8f227331d48e

5e37e720-02ab-499c-8c29-8f227331d48e
Carefully remove cheesecake from springform and serve.
5e37e720-02ab-499c-8c29-8f227331d48e
Keep in fridge for up to 5 days.

Place Almonds, 5 dates and a pinch of salt in food processor and pulse until a sticky mass forms.
62f8bf15-73bb-44ed-abb9-6774f19a87ba
